                <!-- Question 25 - Case Study -->
                <div class="quiz-question case-study">
                    <h4>Question 25: Case Study - Floating-Point Precision Error</h4>
                    <div class="case-study-scenario">
                        <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> A programmer writes: <code>if (0.1 + 0.2 == 0.3)</code> in JavaScript. Surprisingly, this condition evaluates to FALSE! The actual result of 0.1 + 0.2 is 0.30000000000000004.</p>
                    </div>
                    <p>Why does this happen?</p>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q25" value="a">
                            A) It's a bug in JavaScript
                        </label>
